<item>
            <title>[LU-6338] DLC: lnetctl import --del delete the configuration successfully but shows error message</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-6338</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;when running &#8220;lnetctl import FILE --del&#8221;, the command actually delete the configuration successfully but still shows error message&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;the error message indicates &quot;cannot delete route: No such file or directory&quot;, but it did delete the router from the configuration.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;div class=&quot;preformatted panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;preformattedContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre&gt;[root@eagle-54vm3 network-scripts]# lnetctl route show -v
route:
    - net: tcp
      gateway: 192.168.201.101@tcp1
      hop: 1
      priority: 0
      state: up
[root@eagle-54vm3 network-scripts]# lnetctl import client.yaml --del
LNet: Removed LNI 192.168.201.180@tcp1
del:
    - net:
          errno: -22
          descr: &quot;cannot delete network: Invalid argument&quot;
    - net:
          errno: 0
          descr: &quot;success&quot;
    - route:
          errno: -2
          descr: &quot;cannot delete route: No such file or directory&quot;
[root@eagle-54vm3 network-scripts]# lnetctl route show -v
[root@eagle-54vm3 network-scripts]# 
[root@eagle-54vm3 network-scripts]# 
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;</description>
